\subsection{Example of E-text in LaTeX}

You can write complex equations in LaTeX.

\begin{equation}
\left(
\begin{array}{cccc}
1 & 0 & \cdots & 0 \\
0 & 1 & \cdots & 0 \\
\vdots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\
0 & 0 & \cdots & 1
\end{array}
\right)
\end{equation}

\subsection{Example of E-text in LaTeX}

You can write complex equations in LaTeX.

\begin{equation}
\begin{array}{llllll}
& x_1 &&& = & 10 \\
+ \\
& x_1 & + & x_2 & = & 1\\
\cline{2-6}
& 2x_1 & + & x_2 & = & 11
\end{array}
\end{equation}

